<dl>
    <dt>Boot up the iso using a CD/DVD or USB Key to a Live Session</dt>
        <dd>The system should boot properly and load the installer displaying the Welcome dialog with language selection and 'Try FAMILY' and 'Install FAMILY' buttons</dd>
    <dt>Click on the Install FAMILY icon</dt>
        <dd>The 'Preparing to install FAMILY' screen should be displayed</dd>
    <dt>On the screen Preparing to install FAMILY, note the state of each check mark for the following components</dt>
        <dd>
            <ul>
                <li>Your system have at least the amount a space indicated</li>
                <li>(If on a 'laptop'). Is plugged to a power source</li>
                <li>Is connected to the Internet</li>
            </ul>
        </dd>
        <dd>Check marks should represent the state of your system accurately</dd>
    <dt>Click on the continue button</dt>
        <dd>The 'Installation type' screen should be displayed</dd>
    <dt>Note the state of the 'Erase disk and install FAMILY' radio button</dt>
        <dd>The 'Erase disk and install FAMILY' radio button should be checked by default</dd>
    <dt>Click on the continue button (if there is only one hard disk in the system, the button should read 'Install now')</dt>
        <dd>If there is only one hard disk, the installer should skip to the "Where are you?' screen. Otherwise, the 'Installation type' screen should be displayed</dd>
    <dt>If there is only one hard disk, skip to step 10 (On the 'Where are you?' screen...). Otherwise, on the 'Installation type' screen verify that the drive selected on the Select drive list corresponds to the drive on the chart (e.g /dev/sda)</dt>
        <dd>Selected drive should be displayed on the chart</dd>
    <dt>Verify that the full drive space is allocated</dt>
        <dd>Full drive space should be allocated for installation</dd>
    <dt>Click on the Install Now button</dt>
        <dd>The 'Where are you?' screen should be displayed</dd>
    <dt>If your system is connected to the network, note the preselected timezone correspond with your timezone and the city indicated in the text box </dt>
        <dd>The timezone and city displayed should match your timezone and the main city from your area</dd>
    <dt>Select your timezone, and click on the continue button</dt>
        <dd>The 'Keyboard Layout' screen should appear</dd>
        <dd>The proposed keyboard should correspond to your keyboard</dd>
    <dt>Select your keyboard layout and click on continue</dt>
        <dd>The 'Who are you?' screen should appear</dd>
    <dt>Input your initial user details and password (Note admin can not be used - it is a dedicated Linux User)</dt>
        <dd>Name, username and password should be accepted. Additionally, the continue button is enabled</dd>
    <dt>Click on the continue button</dt>
        <dd>The 'Welcome to FAMILY ' slide should be displayed</dd>
        <dd>The slideshow should be entirely in your language</dd> 
    <dt>Wait for the installer to finish</dt>
        <dd>An 'Installation Complete' dialog should appear</dd>
    <dt>Click the Restart now button</dt>
        <dd>GUI should be shut down, a prompt to remove media and press Enter should appear</dd>
    <dt>Remove the disc and press enter</dt>
        <dd>The machine should be rebooted</dd>
    <dt>Allow the machine to reboot</dt>
        <dd>The system should boot properly and loads into FAMILY</dd>
</dl>
<strong>If all actions produce the expected results listed, please <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> a 'passed' result.
    If an action fails, or produces an unexpected result, please <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> a 'failed' result and <a href="../../buginstructions">file a bug</a>. Please be sure to include the bug number when you <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> your result.</strong>
